headline: June Sales at Small Businesses Rise from Last Year, but Consumers Pulled Back Compared to May
summary: MILWAUKEE, July 02, 2025--Fiserv, Inc. (NYSE: FI), a leading global provider of payments and financial services technology, has published the Fiserv Small Business Index for June 2025, with the seasonally-adjusted Index declining two points to 148. Year-over-year sales (+4.4%) remained strong in June while month-over-month sales (-1.4%) declined, reﬂecting a slowdown in consumer activity.
